version: 1.0.0
title: 🌐 Translator Team — Parallel + Voting Multi-Agent System
description: A multi-agent translation system with PARALLEL generation (3 translators) + VOTING (1 judge).
sub_recipes:
  - description: 🎭 Orchestrator — PARALLEL dispatches to 3 translators, then delegates to judge for voting
    name: translator-orchestrator
    path: ./sub/translator-orchestrator.yaml
  - description: 📝 Literal translator — word-for-word, preserves technical terms
    name: translator-literal
    path: ./sub/translator-literal.yaml
  - description: 📖 Literary translator — idiomatic, preserves tone and emotion
    name: translator-literary
    path: ./sub/translator-literary.yaml
  - description: 🔧 Technical translator — preserves domain jargon and precision
    name: translator-technical
    path: ./sub/translator-technical.yaml
  - description: 🏆 Translation judge — scores and VOTES for the best translation
    name: translation-judge
    path: ./sub/translation-judge.yaml
instructions: |
  # translator-team — Multi-Agent System

  This system implements a PARALLEL + VOTING architecture for translation:

  1. **translator-orchestrator** — Entry point. Receives source text + target language.
     PARALLEL dispatches the SAME text to all 3 translators simultaneously.
     After all 3 return, delegates to translation-judge for voting.

  2. **translator-literal** — Word-for-word literal translation. Preserves technical terms.

  3. **translator-literary** — Literary, idiomatic translation. Preserves tone and emotion.

  4. **translator-technical** — Technical translation. Preserves jargon and precision.

  5. **translation-judge** — Scores each candidate on accuracy, fluency, and style-fit.
     VOTES for the best one and returns the winning translation with reasoning.

  ## Usage
  goose run --recipe /path/to/translator-team.yaml --no-session

  The orchestrator will ask for source_text, source_lang, and target_lang.
